Changes from MFIX2010-1 (Date: 02/02/2010) to MFIX2012-1 (Date: 01/19/2012)

New features added:
-------------------

* DEM
  o DMP Parallelization (MPI)
  o SMP Parallelization (OpenMP)
  o Mass inlet and outlet boundary conditions
  o Heat transfer and DES reactive chemistry
  o Cohesion van der Waals force calculation with/without Rumpf corrections to asperities on surface of particles

* Virtual mass
  O Virtual mass force acts to increase the inertia of the dispersed phase, which tends to stabilize simulations of bubbly gas-liquid flows

* GHD (Garzo, Hrenya, and Dufty) granular kinetic theory
  o The GHD model solves mixture momentum and granular energy equations instead of the individual solids phases equations

* Cartesian Grid cut cell technique
  o Partial slip boundary condition
  o K-epsilon wall functions
  o Energy equation
  o Geometry input from STL file and Gambit msh file (3D)
  
* Quadrature method of moments (QMOM)
  o Solves moment transport equations for the particle phase [1]



Changes in existing features:
-----------------------------

* Bug fixes and enhancements:
  o Gfortran compilation: various format statement and line continuation were modified to accommodate gfortran
  o Chi scheme
    - Bug fix: ensure species mass fractions add to one
    - Enhancement: vanishing species no longer degrade the 2nd order scheme to FOU

* Updated documents:
  o Readme file [2]
  o DEM documentation [3]
  o Cartesian grid documentation [4]
  o Summary of MFIX equations [5]



Under Development:
------------------

* MPPIC: Multi-Phase Particle in Cell
* Application of Cartesian cut-cell technique to DEM
* Variable solids density



Project Metrics:
----------------

* Change from 2010-1 Release:
  o 50 new files
  o Nearly 38,000 new lines of code (around 23,000 excluding comments and blank lines)

* 2012-1 Total count:
